    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** stands alone as our elite play (85.94). He is the clear anchor of the lineup, benefitting from a massive 19% SP skill boost against M\u00e1rquez and a favorable 86% stolen base success rate against a pitcher with a notably slow delivery. When paired with the speed-first profile we prioritize at Ghost Ride the WHIP, **Corbin Carroll** is in a tier of his own. Behind him, **Seiya Suzuki** (69.55) and **Brice Turang** (66.73) provide excellent value. **Seiya Suzuki** draws a plus matchup against Sasaki with beneficial wind conditions, while **Brice Turang**\u2019s projected leadoff spot combined with a solid SP skill boost makes him a critical engine for run production today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was undoubtedly **Alex Freeland**, whose 49.73 score fell just short of the efficiency threshold needed to supplant our starters. While **Alex Freeland** offers switch-hitting versatility, his projected ninth-spot in the order dragged down his aggregate score, making him less efficient than the high-upside plays like **Tyler Soderstrom** or **Max Muncy**. Meanwhile, we are closely monitoring the lineup for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Seiya Suzuki**, and **Giancarlo Stanton**; should any of these veterans shift significantly down the batting order, their efficiency scores will crater. We are also steering clear of **Austin Riley** today, as the 2.73 xERA of Wheeler and an elite catcher matchup create a high-risk environment that necessitates a benching. \n\nBeyond our core starters, keep a weather eye on the status of **Mickey Moniak**, who is confirmed for a rainout and must remain benched. We are also managing the potential platoon volatility for **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who faces a tough assignment against Urena (2.35 xERA); while his platoon edge holds his score above 50, his ceiling is limited by the pitcher's dominance. We proceed with confidence, focusing our leverage on the speed-heavy profiles of **James Wood** and **Brice Turang** to maintain our lead in the category wars.",
